30 Scenario-based Questions with Answers (based on covered topics)

1) Q: You run docker run nginx but cannot access the web page from the VM external IP. What do you check?
   A: Check docker ps (is container running), confirm docker run used -p host_port:80, ensure cloud VM firewall/security group allows host_port, use correct HTTP URL, check docker logs.

2) Q: How to run a container in background named web1 mapping VM port 8080 to container 80?
   A: docker run -d --name web1 -p 8080:80 nginx

3) Q: You need persistent web content on host folder /home/ubuntu/site mapped to NGINX html. Command?
   A: docker run -d --name web -p 8080:80 -v /home/ubuntu/site:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro nginx

4) Q: How to remove a running container forcefully?
   A: docker rm -f <container>  (or docker stop <container> && docker rm <container>)

5) Q: You want to execute apt-get update inside a running ubuntu container without attaching interactively. How?
   A: docker exec <container> apt-get update

6) Q: How to start a shell inside a running container named myapp?
   A: docker exec -it myapp /bin/bash   (or /bin/sh if bash not present)

7) Q: You start an interactive ubuntu container with docker run -it ubuntu /bin/bash, exit; container shows as exited. How to restart it?
   A: docker start <container_id_or_name>

8) Q: How to run a one-off command date using alpine image and auto-remove container after run?
   A: docker run --rm alpine date

9) Q: How to see resource usage (CPU and memory) of running containers?
   A: docker stats

10) Q: You need to run 50 short-lived containers for testing—how to spawn them quickly?
    A: Use shell loop: for i in $(seq 1 50); do docker run -d --name demo_$i alpine sleep 1000; done  (adjust sleep or command)

11) Q: How to list all images and show their sizes?
    A: docker images

12) Q: How to count number of running containers from CLI?
    A: docker ps -q | wc -l

13) Q: How to remove unused images and containers to free space?
    A: docker system prune -a   (use carefully, removes unused images/containers/networks)

14) Q: Jenkins is running in container but you cannot find Jenkins config on VM filesystem. Why?
    A: Jenkins runs inside container; its files live in container filesystem unless a volume/bind mount was used. Use docker exec to inspect or mount a host dir as volume.

15) Q: You want container logs but container runs detached. How to get logs?
    A: docker logs <container_name_or_id>

16) Q: How to run a container and assign a specific name to refer easily later?
    A: docker run --name myname <image>

17) Q: You need to enter a running container but the container has no bash, only sh. What do you run?
    A: docker exec -it <container> /bin/sh

18) Q: How to run multiple interdependent services in dev (web + db) easily?
    A: Use Docker Compose with a docker-compose.yml defining services and networks (recommended). Example: define nginx and mongo services and run docker-compose up -d.

19) Q: What command shows stopped containers too?
    A: docker ps -a

20) Q: How to map host port 50000 and 8080 for Jenkins container?
    A: docker run -d --name jenkins -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 jenkins/jenkins:lts

21) Q: You need to inspect container runtime configuration (mounts, env, ports). Command?
    A: docker inspect <container_or_image>

22) Q: How to run a container and keep its filesystem cleaned up afterwards automatically?
    A: Use --rm flag: docker run --rm alpine <command>

23) Q: Image pull fails due to lack of internet inside corporate VM. How to proceed?
    A: Use an internal registry or pre-pull images on a machine with access and push to internal registry; OR enable VM network access/HTTP proxy settings.

24) Q: You want to detach from interactive container but leave it running. You started with docker run -it image /bin/bash. What to do?
    A: In the running shell you can background the shell process (not preferred). Better approach: start container with -d and use docker exec -it to enter when needed.

25) Q: How to view NGINX access logs inside container?
    A: docker exec -it <nginx_container> tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log (or view file with cat/less)

26) Q: How to change a container’s name after creation?
    A: You cannot rename a container easily; best to create new container with --name. (There is docker rename <old> <new> to rename a container.)

27) Q: How to run a container and limit memory usage to 256MB?
    A: docker run -m 256m --memory-swap 256m <image>  (also consider --cpus flag)

28) Q: How to persist Jenkins home on host to survive container removal?
    A: docker run -d --name jenkins -p 8080:8080 -v /path/on/host/jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home jenkins/jenkins:lts

29) Q: How to quickly check whether an image is present locally before a pull?
    A: docker images | grep <imagename>  OR docker image inspect <image>:<tag> (inspect fails if not present)

30) Q: You started many containers but need to stop them all at once. How?
    A: docker stop $(docker ps -q)   # stop all running containers; to remove all: docker rm $(docker ps -aq)

